--- Birch and Swinnerton-Dyer Conjecture (Clay Millennium Problem) ---
  The BSD conjecture states: for an elliptic curve E/Q,
    rank(E(Q)) = ord_{s=1} L(E, s)

  J_0(143) is an abelian variety of dimension 13 (not a single elliptic curve)
